<!-- 1.2.41 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 1.2.41</span>
Let $S$ be a $\kappa$-distributive inverse semigroup, and suppose $F\subseteq S$ is compatible, $|F|<\kappa$. If $z\in S$ is such that $z\land f$ exists for all $f\in F$, then $z\land\left(\bigvee F\right)$ exists and
<div class='equation'>\[
z\land(\bigvee F)=\bigvee(z\land F),\qquad\text{ where }z\land F=\left\{z\land f:f\in F\right\}.
\]</div>
</p>
</div>